    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-12T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-12T11:00:00-05:00" n="134"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 868.00/117</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Droppers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-12T18:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 12, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 12, 9.20 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>354. King still in Athens owing to lack of swift British cruiser, his suite
                    consisting of forty persons. Dense crowd around Palace asserting that they will
                    not let King depart. <persName corresp="#p_A1">Alexander</persName> took oath at
                    1 p.m. to-day. Italian Minister visited <persName corresp="#p_JCC1"
                        >Jonnart</persName> stating that past friction between Italy and Allies must
                    be forgotten and he will cooperate with <persName corresp="#p_JCC1"
                        >Jonnart</persName> to end confusion in Greece. King and suite have just
                    left Palace for Piraeus. French soldiers approaching Athens.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Droppers</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
